result.name: Star of Canton Restaurant

reviews.text: A decent Chinese restaurant serving Cantonese cuisines and dim sum. Prices are moderate and the quality of food is good. The fried rice is well prepared as well as the fried shredded pork noodles. Make sure you do prior booking during Sunday and public holidays.

Went to one in Sheung Wan and liked it. So this one was in Causeway Bay. The dim sum dishes were the usual suspects, but fried beef noodle with gravy was also nice. For winter we also tried fried sticky rice. I would say it was very clean and it felt less busy than those in Central. The best part was you can make a reservation! No stress!
If you manage to get a window table, you can enjoy delicious dim sum with incredible view over old the part of cwb. Very crowded during weekends!
Food & service are average but price is a bit on the high end even during morning discount hours.

Not sure why the negative reviews. Because of chipped plates? Who cares... the food is good, and the prices reasonable. They have an English picture menu for some dishes and English on part of the dim sum menu. Plus the waiters are patient while you Google translate. Overall a worthy spot for lunch. It is surely a lively spot (noisy, but this is not meant to be a library).

result.name: Lee Theatre

reviews.text: This area of Hong Kong was recently redone. The shopping area is really cute with tons of stores. It is very clean the sales people are very helpful it's a few blocks away from times square mall. It's has lots of up  scale stores they are all very nice there is multiple buildings in the Lee Theater area so check the address to make sure you are in the correct building

Large shopping mall which is part of the Lee Gardens concept. Nice and functional, but not really with to much of a soul of is own or anything else to do really than to shop and eat. Functional rather than fantastic.

Your dinning place. Lots of nice restaurants in this building. 

Lower level are clothing shops. Upper levels are all restaurants. Take the lifts to go up to the higher levels.

this is a place to visit especially if you love shopping at UNIQLO. Several floors of UNIQLO assures you way better variety and stocks. Being located in causeway bay, it is convenient to explore from one shopping mall to another since the malls are just adjacent to each other.
The once iconic landmark theater turned shopping and dining center.

result.formatted_address: 香港銅鑼灣波斯富街99號
result.name: 利寶閣

reviews.text: 這裡食物味道下錯😋😋

抵食。好食。
試過幾次午市㸃心放題(銅鑼灣, 尖沙嘴, 上環), 自己和朋友家人都覺得銅鑼灣店是最好的(服務好, 㸃心也是最好食的分店)。

2小時晚市放題(人不多的時候,可以坐3小時)。抵食好食。Delicious。
花膠響螺雞湯, 鮑魚花菇, 花雕蒸奄仔蟹, 片皮鴨, 醉蝦, 蒜香蝦, 水煮牛肉, 水煮魚, 石岐乳鴿, 脆皮燒腩仔, 上湯淨雲呑, 乾炒安格斯牛河, 㰖角肉骨, 楊枝甘露, 紅豆冰, 冰糖胡蘆,...
   調味好, 炒功皆, 火候足。大廚抵讚, 員工服務也不錯。
利寶閣在利舞台21樓，是中菜館，午市由11點至4點，大約$148 1 位，點心任點任食，每位有花膠 灌湯餃及 酥皮鮑魚撻送，其他點心應有盡有，製作認真，材料新鮮，不會因為任點而將貨就價，是值得一試，不過要預時閒等位。
四川晚反任食，某d食物幾好，其它就一般，性價比不高
中菜、飲茶。覺得點心好味！
